The management of the University of Port Harcourt has announced the sudden postponement of the 33rd convocation earlier slated for April 2, 2022. The postponement was contained in a statement signed by the university spokesman, Sam Kpenu, through the Registrar, Dr Gloria Chindah. No reason was given for the postponement and the university had yet to give a new date. The statement reads, “The 33rd combined convocation ceremony for the award of diplomas, first degrees, postgraduate diplomas, higher degrees, honorary degrees and prize presentation earlier scheduled to hold on the 1st and 2nd of April, 2022, has been postponed by the Management of the University of Port Harcourt. “The Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Georgewill regrets the inconveniences this new development may have caused the public, graduands, their parents, sponsors, the stakeholders and esteemed invited guests. “A new date will be communicated in due course.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com